    <text id="F3518T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>George Melott explains his illness and whereabouts before an arrest in Ohio.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
               

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-06-25">June 25, 1864</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>

                <p>George Melott says he came out with the 126th Penna. Vols-a 9 months regt-was
                    sent home to McConnelsburg Pa. From Antietam MD, in September, with sick
                    furlough for two weeks, did not get better &amp; was taken with rheumatism
                    &amp; when he got over that the time of his regiment had expired, he wrote
                    to his colonel of the circumstances in which he was placed but never rec'd a
                    reply-was arrested the 3d of February 64 at Canton, Ohio &amp; sent to
                    Cincinatti and thence via Harrisburg to this place.</p>

                <p>I approve that the above is true and that I have the rheumatism so bad that it is
                    impossible for me to write my name.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>George X (his mark) Melott</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
